author: stsp
msg: On the svn-auth-x590 branch, start showing cert info with the new x509 parser.
This is preliminary, the parser API still needs changes (e.g. it should return
something like an apr_hash_t instead of the custom x509 struct).
* subversion/libsvn_subr/x509.h
(x509parse_dn_gets): Declare.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/x509parse.c
(svn_x509_parse_cert): Set output paramter before returning.
(x509parse_dn_gets): Temporarily restore this function from tropicssl.
This will be replaced soon (and not only because this code is using
snprintf() unsafely).
* subversion/svn/auth-cmd.c
(show_cert): New helper function which shows information obtained
from a PEM cert (base64-encoded), as stored in the auth cache.
(list_credential): Use show_cert(). Disable code showing cert info
stored in the config hash.
